(828, '687', '2', '465', '1304', 'No mss. Reported in [I] and [F].', '[JC: possibly printed in Suleymaniye Reisülküttab 1142 pp.1-30 (1275H). Title in Turkish catalogue: Risale fi Beyani\'ş-Şeria ve\'t-Tarika ve\'l-Hakika ve\'l-Ma\'rif. Also listed is  Suleymaniye Tahir Ağa Tekke 51 pp.82-84 with title: Risale fi Beyani\'ş-Şeria ve\'t-Tarika ve\'l-Hakika.] [Anonymous works with title Risale fi’ş-şeri‘a ve’t-tarika ve’l-hakika are found in the following collections, each of which contains at least one IA-related work: Laleli 3653 and Trabzon İl H  2959. For the latter see http://ktp.isam.org.tr/ktpgenel/recordlistb.php?-skip=0&amp;-max=50&amp;KtpKodu=0121&amp;Bolum=&amp;Demirba%C5%9F=002959 ] [C. Addas has suggested this work was a form of FM chapters 68-72 (on \'Ibadat) gathered as an autonomous work on the initiative of IA. She notes that Murtadâ al-Zabîdî in his Ithâf al-sâdât al-mutaqqîn cites a work of IA under the title Kitâb al-sharî‘a a number of times and in each case the citation is similar to FM but begins with the formula wa l-haqîqa (which does not occur in FM). Furthermore she recalls that the editor Reichmuth indicates that Brockelmann suggested a possible ms in GAL I.446 (579?) no. 96: namely, Cairo I, VII, 528, with title Shams al-tariqa fi bayan al-shari\'a wa-l-haqiqa (which is the title of RG 670). That same title is used for a work attributed to IA in Kashf al-Zunun. There is a ms of a work with that title attributed to IA in Topkapi Ahmet III 1393 dated 1478CE (i.e. 882H or 883H): Şemsü\'t-Tarika fi Beyani\'ş-Şeria ve\'l-Hakika. See also RG 670 for this title - OY regarded it as a doubtful attribution. Having examined another copy, Azhar (1272) 43010 (1031H), CA has determined that is not by IA and neither can it be the work quoted by Murtadâ al-Zabîdî.]', 'OY_OIL_BP189_Ara_Y_all_v2_2_RG_entries.pdf', '43', 'R', 'K. al-Sharīʿa wa-l-ṭarīqa wa-l-ḥaqīqa', 'K. al-Sharīʿa wa-l-ṭarīqa wa-l-ḥaqīqa (1304)<br/>K. al-Sharīʿa wa-l-ḥaqīqa (1305)<br/>', 'كتا